ner, Olustee, Bermuda Hundred — and served alongside the 54th Massachusetts at the assault on Fort Wagner. Specific battle service for Butler not yet researched."},{"number":2,"category":"career","header":"President of Home National Bank of Meriden","body":"After the war he returned to Meriden and entered banking, rising to the presidency of Home National Bank. He died at New Haven on December 21, 1894, aged fifty, and was buried at Walnut Grove Cemetery in Meriden."}],"quotes":[],"sources":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"slug":"edwin-butler-1844"}},"burialCemetery":null,"institutionsById":{},"crossConnections":[]}